    Note right of browser: User types a new note and clicks "Save"

    browser->>browser: JavaScript prevents default form submission
    Note right of browser: spa.js captures the input

    browser->>browser: JavaScript creates a new note object (content, date)
    Note right of browser: The new note is added to the JavaScript's internal data structure

    browser->>browser: JavaScript updates the displayed notes on the page using the DOM API
    Note right of browser: The user sees the new note instantly without a page reload

    browser->>server: POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note_spa
    Note right of browser: JavaScript sends the new note data as JSON in the request body
    Note right of browser: Content-Type header is set to application/json
